01:08:20.721 --> 01:08:24.724
Maybe they're rolled by little Albanians
in Bujanovac. but who cares?

996
01:08:24.975 --> 01:08:26.643
And this is just one thing.

997
01:08:26.852 --> 01:08:29.395
There's perfume and cologne.

998
01:08:29.647 --> 01:08:33.483
brandy. port. Calvados.
truffles. caviar.

999
01:08:33.818 --> 01:08:35.443
Is all that legal?

1000
01:08:36.153 --> 01:08:39.197
Baby. this is Wild West.

1001
01:08:39.532 --> 01:08:40.949
Who has time chasing after

1002
01:08:41.033 --> 01:08:43.910
some fucking Serbian guy
five inches tall

1003
01:08:43.994 --> 01:08:45.870
over a few cigars and some wine?

1004
01:08:46.664 --> 01:08:50.125
My brother and I
are now in seven small cities

1005
01:08:50.209 --> 01:08:52.502
around the world. Seven!

1006
01:08:53.462 --> 01:08:54.629
Paul. listen.

1007
01:08:54.713 --> 01:08:56.631
Anything you want. I can get for you.

1008
01:08:56.924 --> 01:08:58.258
Anything. anytime.

1009
01:08:58.342 --> 01:08:59.676
Excuse me a minute.

1010
01:09:13.816 --> 01:09:14.816
Hello.

1011
01:09:18.112 --> 01:09:19.696
Can I talk to you for a minute?

1012
01:09:23.284 --> 01:09:25.785
"Na-pro-sien. " What this do?

1013
01:09:33.836 --> 01:09:36.838
Naproxen. It's an anti-inflammatory.

1014
01:09:37.089 --> 01:09:39.632
- It's for pain and swelling.
- Ah.

1015
01:09:43.971 --> 01:09:46.306
And this one? What this one do?

1016
01:09:47.308 --> 01:09:50.268
Well. Vicodin. That's also a painkiller.

1017
01:09:51.187 --> 01:09:53.521
But you want to be really
careful with that one.

1018
01:09:53.606 --> 01:09:55.523
Painkiller? Painkiller good.

1019
01:09:55.608 --> 01:09:58.568
Listen. This is not my apartment.

1020
01:09:59.153 --> 01:10:01.070
and I'm sure you're probably
in a lot of pain.

1021
01:10:01.155 --> 01:10:03.323
but you shouldn't steal pills.

1022
01:10:03.699 --> 01:10:05.200
I no steal.

1023
01:10:05.284 --> 01:10:06.659
They too old. no good.

1024
01:10:06.744 --> 01:10:09.621
Mr. Dušan. he say me okay
I take away thing.

1025
01:10:10.080 --> 01:10:12.081
Pill for sick friend.

1026
01:10:19.590 --> 01:10:22.425
Okay. I finish now. Bathroom clean.

1027
01:10:25.596 --> 01:10:27.764
Well. whatever's wrong
with your "friend."

1028
01:10:27.848 --> 01:10:30.600
I can see that you have
a really. really bad prosthetic foot.

1029
01:10:30.684 --> 01:10:33.186
I'm sure it's causing you pain
in your right hip and knee.

1030
01:10:33.270 --> 01:10:35.605
probably your other knee.
your lower back.

1031
01:10:36.857 --> 01:10:39.734
How you know these thing? You a doctor?

1032
01:10:40.277 --> 01:10:41.778
Occupational therapist.

1033
01:10:43.489 --> 01:10:45.990
Wait a minute. I know you.

1034
01:10:47.576 --> 01:10:48.576
You're the... Oh. my God!

1035
01:10:49.036 --> 01:10:50.912
You're that woman from
a couple years ago.

1036
01:10:50.996 --> 01:10:52.121
the dissident.

1037
01:10:52.206 --> 01:10:55.083
from Thailand or something?
What's your name?

1038
01:10:55.834 --> 01:10:57.835
Tran Ngoc Lan. Vietnam.

1039
01:10:57.920 --> 01:11:01.256
Tran Ngoc Lan from Vietnam.
Yes. that's right!

1040
01:11:01.340 --> 01:11:04.717
And I remember that you lost
your leg below the knee.

1041
01:11:04.802 --> 01:11:06.594
That's... That's you.

1042
01:11:07.221 --> 01:11:08.221
Wow.

1043
01:11:12.142 --> 01:11:13.351
Dušan...

1044
01:11:13.435 --> 01:11:15.770
Hey. do you know who this is here?

1045
01:11:15.938 --> 01:11:18.106
Of course. The famous Ngoc Lan Tran.

1046
01:11:18.274 --> 01:11:20.275
Dramatic escape from Vietnamese prison.

1047
01:11:20.359 --> 01:11:23.278
almost died so now
she can clean my house.

1048
01:11:24.196 --> 01:11:27.240
America. Big land of opportunity!

1049
01:11:27.533 --> 01:11:29.367
(BOTH LAUGH)

1050
01:11:32.913 --> 01:11:34.914
Push up. Push again. Push. push. push.

1051
01:11:34.999 --> 01:11:37.417
Okay. that's it. Now take your heel
back towards you.

1052
01:11:37.710 --> 01:11:39.419
Even harder if you can.

1053
01:11:39.586 --> 01:11:40.753
Even... Yeah.

1054
01:11:41.088 --> 01:11:42.088
Yeah.

1055
01:11:42.589 --> 01:11:44.215
Put your hand right here.

1056
01:11:44.300 --> 01:11:45.300
Feel that. okay?

1057
01:11:45.384 --> 01:11:46.801
Feel that crunching? You hear it?

1058
01:11:46.885 --> 01:11:50.638
That's arthritis.
That's already pretty bad.

1059
01:11:51.015 --> 01:11:52.015
Paul?

1060
01:11:52.474 --> 01:11:54.100
You're full of surprises.

1061
01:11:54.184 --> 01:11:57.478
You can do this. but you work
shit job answering phones?

1062
01:11:57.563 --> 01:11:59.605
When I moved down here.
I didn't think I'd be working.

1063
01:11:59.690 --> 01:12:01.107
so I let my license expire.

1064
01:12:01.191 --> 01:12:03.776
and now I'd have to get it
in a whole other state.

1065
01:12:03.861 --> 01:12:04.986
It's a boring story.

1066
01:12:07.656 --> 01:12:09.157
I hate to say it.

1067
01:12:09.241 --> 01:12:10.533
but if you don't do
something pretty soon.

1068
01:12:10.617 --> 01:12:12.035
you're going to need a new knee.

1069
01:12:12.119 --> 01:12:13.995
Maybe even a new hip.

1070
01:12:14.079 --> 01:12:16.205
You've got to go to
a specialist as soon as you can

1071
01:12:16.290 --> 01:12:17.415
and get a whole new foot.

1072
01:12:17.499 --> 01:12:18.583
In the meantime.

1073
01:12:18.709 --> 01:12:21.210
I could make some adjustments
on the existing prosthetic

1074
01:12:21.295 --> 01:12:23.713
and maybe give you some pointers
on how to walk better.

1075
01:12:23.881 --> 01:12:26.883
I just hate to see you needlessly suffer
after all you've been through.

1076
01:12:27.051 --> 01:12:29.552
Okay. I finish work. you come with me.

1077
01:12:29.928 --> 01:12:32.096
No. I could get my tools.
I can do it right here.

1078
01:12:32.389 --> 01:12:35.641
No. I say you before.
My friend sick. need pill.

1079
01:12:35.809 --> 01:12:38.186
You come with me my house. help her.

1080
01:12:38.437 --> 01:12:39.854
You help her.

1081
01:12:40.230 --> 01:12:42.065
I don't think I was clear.

1082
01:12:42.232 --> 01:12:44.776
I can help you with this.
but I'm not a doctor.

1083
01:12:44.860 --> 01:12:46.486
so your friend.
whatever's wrong with her.

1084
01:12:46.570 --> 01:12:48.237
she's got to go
to a clinic or a hospital.

1085
01:12:48.405 --> 01:12:49.530
No! Clinic no good.

1086
01:12:49.615 --> 01:12:51.491
I bring her clinic. wait too long time.

1087
01:12:51.575 --> 01:12:54.911
Stupid doctor say no help for her.
No do nothing!

1088
01:12:55.037 --> 01:12:58.790
He no good stupid doctor
in big world. now he small.

1089
01:12:59.249 --> 01:13:00.750
You come with me.

1090
01:13:01.377 --> 01:13:03.044
You come with me now.

1091
01:13:03.504 --> 01:13:04.504
Uh...

1092
01:13:07.174 --> 01:13:08.257
Come.

1093
01:13:17.434 --> 01:13:18.851
(MAN COUGHING)

1094
01:13:25.901 --> 01:13:28.653
PAUL: You live near here?
NGOC LAN: No. still far.

1095
01:13:30.072 --> 01:13:32.073
Maybe we should grab a car.

1096
01:13:32.908 --> 01:13:35.076
No need car. Take bus.

1097
01:13:47.881 --> 01:13:49.715
PAUL: If you don't mind my asking.

1098
01:13:49.883 --> 01:13:51.759
you were so famous a couple years ago.

1099
01:13:51.844 --> 01:13:53.594
I mean. everybody was talking about you.

1100
01:13:53.929 --> 01:13:57.932
I just would've thought you would be
giving speeches or writing books.

1101
01:13:58.308 --> 01:14:00.560
How'd you wind up cleaning houses?

1102
01:14:00.894 --> 01:14:02.395
Need money for live.

1103
01:14:02.980 --> 01:14:05.648
After TV box.
I stay hospital so long time.

1104
01:14:05.732 --> 01:14:06.899
Almost die.

1105
01:14:07.192 --> 01:14:09.986
Then three host family.
But too much problem.

1106
01:14:10.070 --> 01:14:11.404
Leisureland people too selfish.

1107
01:14:11.822 --> 01:14:14.907
Better I live only me. work job.
make money. Easy.

1108
01:14:58.911 --> 01:15:00.661
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1109
01:15:36.198 --> 01:15:38.533
Hey! You! Come!

1110
01:15:39.326 --> 01:15:40.409
Come!

1111
01:15:49.836 --> 01:15:51.420
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1112
01:16:05.143 --> 01:16:07.436
(MEN SPEAKING SPANISH ON TV)

1113
01:16:43.515 --> 01:16:44.515
NGOC LAN: You!

1114
01:16:44.891 --> 01:16:47.560
Come on! No time for baby dream.

1115
01:16:50.397 --> 01:16:52.315
May I ask how high we're going?

1116
01:16:52.399 --> 01:16:54.233
- Seven floor.
- Seven?

1117
01:16:54.401 --> 01:16:57.486
- Can we use the elevator?
- No elevator.

1118
01:17:06.913 --> 01:17:08.497
(BABY CRYING)

1119
01:17:09.249 --> 01:17:12.084
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1120
01:17:26.767 --> 01:17:28.100
Take the shoe.

1121
01:17:34.024 --> 01:17:35.483
Hola. Gladys.

1122
01:17:39.863 --> 01:17:42.198
This lady Gladys. Gladys my friend.

1123
01:17:42.282 --> 01:17:43.449
She very sick.

1124
01:17:43.784 --> 01:17:45.368
Gladys. how you feel?

1125
01:17:45.535 --> 01:17:48.037
Cómo estás? Cómo estás?

1126
01:17:48.121 --> 01:17:49.413
I bring food for you.

1127
01:17:49.915 --> 01:17:52.583
I bring doctor. This man doctor.

1128
01:17:53.251 --> 01:17:55.294
(NGOC LAN SPEAKING SPANISH)

1129
01:17:58.090 --> 01:18:00.633
This lady Gladys alone. No have nobody.

1130
01:18:00.717 --> 01:18:02.885
Husband die Mexico when they make small.

1131
01:18:02.969 --> 01:18:05.262
Stupid people forget take
the gold from the teeth.

1132
01:18:05.347 --> 01:18:06.389
Head explode.

1133
01:18:06.723 --> 01:18:09.058
- What?
- Husband head explode.

1134
01:18:09.559 --> 01:18:12.228
Head explode! From teeth.

1135
01:18:12.729 --> 01:18:14.480
She come alone. no money.

1136
01:18:14.564 --> 01:18:17.233
I meet her. she housekeeper
first host family.

1137
01:18:17.317 --> 01:18:20.403
Rich Leisureland people.
Now she sick. no more work.

1138
01:18:20.779 --> 01:18:22.446
Okay. you take care for her.

1139
01:18:26.451 --> 01:18:28.119
I can't do anything for her.

1140
01:18:28.453 --> 01:18:31.747
That woman is really sick.
It looks like she might die!

1141
01:18:31.957 --> 01:18:33.624
Oh. yeah. she die soon.

1142
01:18:33.792 --> 01:18:36.210
Cancer. Cancer all over stomach.

1143
01:18:36.503 --> 01:18:39.922
I be with her she die.
Most bad thing die alone.

1144
01:18:57.816 --> 01:18:59.734
Come on. Be like doctor.

1145
01:19:02.404 --> 01:19:04.071
Make her feel good.

1146
01:19:07.993 --> 01:19:09.326
<i>Hola. señora.</i>

1147
01:19:10.036 --> 01:19:13.122
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

1148
01:19:19.588 --> 01:19:21.338
Which pill most good for her?

1149
01:19:22.424 --> 01:19:23.716
(IN ENGLISH) I have no idea.

1150
01:19:23.800 --> 01:19:25.718
But you know thing.

1151
01:19:25.802 --> 01:19:27.470
Which pill most strong?

1152
01:19:31.391 --> 01:19:32.475
Percocet.

1153
01:19:33.477 --> 01:19:36.228
Yes. Percocet. Very good for pain.

1154
01:19:36.605 --> 01:19:39.190
How much? Two? Four? Five? How much?

1155
01:19:40.275 --> 01:19:41.442
Try two.

1156
01:19:42.068 --> 01:19:44.904
Two? This lady very sick. Pill old.

1157
01:19:45.238 --> 01:19:46.572
We give four.

1158
01:19:50.035 --> 01:19:51.702
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1159
01:19:53.371 --> 01:19:54.705
Gracias. doctor.

1160
01:19:57.876 --> 01:19:59.960
Have you tried to
move her every couple hours.

1161
01:20:00.045 --> 01:20:01.879
so she doesn't get bedsores?

1162
01:20:03.298 --> 01:20:05.049
We should probably do that.

1163
01:20:07.010 --> 01:20:09.220
- Go. There you go. Okay.
- (GROANING)

1164
01:20:09.304 --> 01:20:11.430
See? You know thing.

1165
01:20:18.980 --> 01:20:21.982
Thank you. Mr. Dušan friend.
You help Gladys good.

1166
01:20:22.400 --> 01:20:23.901
Okay. Well.

1167
01:20:24.736 --> 01:20:26.153
let's make those adjustments.

1168
01:20:26.238 --> 01:20:27.905
If you just want to slip off your foot.

1169
01:20:28.073 --> 01:20:29.740
No. no foot. I tired.

1170
01:20:29.908 --> 01:20:32.660
You go away. I stay with
Gladys. you go away now.

1171
01:20:33.411 --> 01:20:35.830
- Really? I mean...
- I tired. You go away.

1172
01:20:35.914 --> 01:20:37.039
Okay.

1173
01:20:37.123 --> 01:20:38.874
Some other time. I guess.

1174
01:20:39.459 --> 01:20:42.044
I just don't know
when I'm gonna see you again.

1175
01:20:43.380 --> 01:20:45.548
Thursday. You come Thursday. okay?

1176
01:20:45.966 --> 01:20:48.968
Thursday morning
you come fix leg. 10:00.

1177
01:20:51.972 --> 01:20:53.722
Thursday at 10:00.

1178
01:20:58.979 --> 01:21:02.481
My name's Paul. by the way.
Paul Safranek.

1179
01:21:12.033 --> 01:21:13.117
Let's see...

1180
01:21:13.535 --> 01:21:15.870
The extra-large is available in

1181
01:21:15.954 --> 01:21:20.833
glacier. pebble. tulip. cayenne.
moss and aubergine.

1182
01:21:21.418 --> 01:21:24.169
<i>WOMAN: Cayenne? Is that like red?</i>

1183
01:21:24.754 --> 01:21:28.424
It's... It's a brownish red.
It's more like brick.

1184
01:21:28.508 --> 01:21:30.509
<i>No. I don't like brick.</i>

1185
01:21:31.011 --> 01:21:33.012
<i>Do you think moss is pretty?</i>

1186
01:21:33.430 --> 01:21:35.014
You know. I don't know. lady.

1187
01:21:35.098 --> 01:21:37.057
Why don't you just pick a color. please?

1188
01:21:37.392 --> 01:21:39.393
<i>Don't be short with me!</i>

1189
01:21:39.769 --> 01:21:41.270
What did you say?

1190
01:21:41.605 --> 01:21:44.064
(MEN SPEAKING SPANISH ON TV)

1191
01:21:53.283 --> 01:21:54.283
Hi.

1192
01:21:56.244 --> 01:21:57.244
Shoe.

1193
01:22:00.916 --> 01:22:01.999
Where's Gladys?

1194
01:22:02.667 --> 01:22:03.792
Oh. she die.

1195
01:22:04.002 --> 01:22:05.210
No. Oh...

1196
01:22:05.295 --> 01:22:06.503
I'm so sorry.

1197
01:22:07.005 --> 01:22:09.173
I think maybe I give her too much pill.

1198
01:22:09.424 --> 01:22:12.009
Anyway. she die very happy. smiling.

1199
01:22:13.178 --> 01:22:15.554
- Okay. you fix foot now.
- (SOFTLY) What?

1200
01:22:16.806 --> 01:22:17.973
(GRUNTS)

1201
01:22:19.601 --> 01:22:20.809
You do quick.

1202
01:22:21.144 --> 01:22:24.647
Must clean house soon. one hour.
You do quick.

1203
01:22:26.024 --> 01:22:27.316
Quick!

1204
01:22:33.198 --> 01:22:34.239
Oh.

1205
01:22:34.407 --> 01:22:35.741
Thank you. very nice.

1206
01:22:35.992 --> 01:22:38.661
You finish soon. okay? I very busy.

1207
01:22:38.995 --> 01:22:40.329
I'm getting there.

1208
01:22:47.087 --> 01:22:49.088
I guess you like butterflies.

1209
01:22:51.007 --> 01:22:52.007
Butterflies?

1210
01:22:52.175 --> 01:22:54.259
Yes. I like very much.

1211
01:22:54.844 --> 01:22:59.431
When I little girl. my father.
he take me. my sister go see butterfly.

1212
01:22:59.975 --> 01:23:02.309
Near my village they live in the tree.

1213
01:23:02.811 --> 01:23:04.061
You know.

1214
01:23:04.312 --> 01:23:08.148
they fly cold place
to hot place every year.

1215
01:23:08.525 --> 01:23:10.859
Stay tree. then go away. come back.

1216
01:23:13.071 --> 01:23:14.405
Migrating butterflies.

1217
01:23:14.698 --> 01:23:16.532
- Yes.
- That sounds beautiful.

1218
01:23:17.784 --> 01:23:19.785
How do you say "butterfly"
in Vietnamese?

1219
01:23:20.829 --> 01:23:21.870
(SPEAKS VIETNAMESE)

1220
01:23:22.664 --> 01:23:23.747
(MISPRONOUNCES)

1221
01:23:25.625 --> 01:23:27.042
(SPEAKS VIETNAMESE SLOWLY)

1222
01:23:29.254 --> 01:23:30.254
(REPEATS)

1223
01:23:30.338 --> 01:23:31.755
You miss your village?

1224
01:23:32.173 --> 01:23:33.507
No more village.

1225
01:23:34.009 --> 01:23:37.261
Government make the people
go away. put water all over.

1226
01:23:37.429 --> 01:23:39.680
All over everywhere! Too much water.

1227
01:23:39.973 --> 01:23:41.306
Too much water?

1228
01:23:41.474 --> 01:23:43.642
Big water for make electricity.

1229
01:23:43.810 --> 01:23:44.810
Oh. a dam.

1230
01:23:44.978 --> 01:23:47.312
Yes. dam. They make dam.

1231
01:23:48.064 --> 01:23:50.232
Many village no more.

1232
01:23:51.026 --> 01:23:52.943
That's why I go prison.

1233
01:23:53.069 --> 01:23:55.487
Me. my sister make protest.

1234
01:23:55.905 --> 01:23:57.823
- Big protest.
- Uh-huh.

1235
01:23:59.325 --> 01:24:01.160
Well. where's your sister now?

1236
01:24:02.662 --> 01:24:04.580
She die prison.

1237
01:24:09.836 --> 01:24:13.338
Too cold. chest fill up bad. She die.

1238
01:24:23.516 --> 01:24:24.850
(CLATTERING)

1239
01:24:27.812 --> 01:24:29.730
- What happened?
- Nothing.

1240
01:24:31.691 --> 01:24:33.192
Just give me a minute.

1241
01:24:33.318 --> 01:24:35.402
- What you do?
- No. nothing. nothing.

1242
01:24:36.071 --> 01:24:37.237
NGOC LAN: You stupid man!

1243
01:24:37.322 --> 01:24:39.698
You needed a new foot anyway.
We'll get you a good one.

1244
01:24:39.783 --> 01:24:41.158
Is that so hard to understand?

1245
01:24:41.242 --> 01:24:43.660
- Jesus!
- No say Jesus bad way.

1246
01:24:44.079 --> 01:24:45.954
Now I'm supposed to watch my language?

1247
01:24:46.039 --> 01:24:47.414
You're worse than my mother.

1248
01:24:47.582 --> 01:24:49.041
I feel sorry for your mother.

1249
01:24:49.125 --> 01:24:51.752
I sure she suffer too much
for your fault.

1250
01:24:56.800 --> 01:24:58.342
Not do so fast!

1251
01:24:58.676 --> 01:25:01.845
Vacuum cleaner need time
same direction clean good.

1252
01:25:07.560 --> 01:25:08.685
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

1253
01:25:11.981 --> 01:25:13.190
And you can take these.

1254
01:25:13.274 --> 01:25:16.235
These are samosas
from a couple of days ago.

1255
01:25:16.903 --> 01:25:19.488
NGOC LAN: Thank you. yes.
I take all these.

1256
01:25:20.156 --> 01:25:22.074
Oh! I think this is saag paneer.

1257
01:25:22.158 --> 01:25:24.076
It might be a little bit old.

1258
01:25:26.371 --> 01:25:27.579
(SNIFFS) Oh...

1259
01:25:27.664 --> 01:25:30.165
In prison we die for such food.

1260
01:25:33.753 --> 01:25:36.004
Okay. Not too many
leftover entrees today.

1261
01:25:36.089 --> 01:25:37.756
but I threw in lots of
baked potato soup.

1262
01:25:38.508 --> 01:25:39.842
Thank you. Roger.

1263
01:25:40.051 --> 01:25:41.176
ROGER: There you go.

1264
01:25:42.095 --> 01:25:44.221
Hey. you finally got yourself
a helper. huh. Ngoc Lan?

1265
01:25:44.889 --> 01:25:47.224
This Paul. He break my foot.

1266
01:25:49.394 --> 01:25:50.477
How'd you manage that. buddy?

1267
01:25:50.562 --> 01:25:51.979
It's a long story. We're sorting it out.

1268
01:25:52.147 --> 01:25:53.647
NGOC LAN: He stupid!

1269
01:25:54.732 --> 01:25:56.817
(TV PLAYING)

1270
01:26:04.909 --> 01:26:07.244
Hola. Señor Càrdenas.

1271
01:26:07.328 --> 01:26:09.997
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

1272
01:26:25.930 --> 01:26:28.390
(IN ENGLISH) Okay. Over here. This way.

1273
01:26:34.397 --> 01:26:36.064
(ALL SPEAKING SPANISH)

1274
01:26:37.150 --> 01:26:38.400
PAUL: (IN ENGLISH)
Oh. that looks really painful.

1275
01:26:38.610 --> 01:26:39.902
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1276
01:26:44.199 --> 01:26:46.450
I bet that's ringworm.

1277
01:26:46.534 --> 01:26:48.118
which I don't know
how to say in Spanish.

1278
01:26:48.203 --> 01:26:52.206
But ringworm is a fungus.
so you want it dry.

1279
01:26:52.373 --> 01:26:54.291
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

1280
01:26:55.585 --> 01:26:57.544
(IN ENGLISH) And I'll see if I can
pick something up

1281
01:26:57.629 --> 01:26:59.338
at the drugstore
and bring it for him tomorrow.

1282
01:26:59.422 --> 01:27:00.589
Yes. you bring.

1283
01:27:00.757 --> 01:27:03.008
(ALL SPEAKING SPANISH)

1284
01:27:05.094 --> 01:27:06.303
(IN ENGLISH) Okay. next. Let's go.

1285
01:27:06.387 --> 01:27:07.971
(BOTH SPEAKING SPANISH)

1286
01:27:08.056 --> 01:27:09.973
NGOC LAN: Let's go!
PAUL: I'm coming.

1287
01:27:10.725 --> 01:27:12.351
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1288
01:27:14.062 --> 01:27:15.145
NGOC LAN: Take care for him.

1289
01:27:15.230 --> 01:27:16.480
<i>- See you next time.
- Gracias.</i>

1290
01:27:18.483 --> 01:27:20.067
So that's it? We go home now?

1291
01:27:20.235 --> 01:27:22.444
Now we go church pray Jesus.

1292
01:27:22.904 --> 01:27:25.113
(ALL SINGING IN SPANISH)

1293
01:27:39.128 --> 01:27:40.921
(ALL CONTINUE SINGING IN SPANISH)

1294
01:27:52.392 --> 01:27:55.060
You come back tomorrow. pick me up 8:00.

1295
01:27:55.144 --> 01:27:56.979
Yeah. okay. I'll be here.

1296
01:28:06.823 --> 01:28:08.282
NGOC LAN: Good morning. Mr. Dušan.

1297
01:28:08.366 --> 01:28:09.908
We come clean for you.

1298
01:28:13.413 --> 01:28:15.247
(LAUGHING)

1299
01:28:30.513 --> 01:28:33.515
Answering telephones was not
dignified enough for you.

1300
01:28:33.599 --> 01:28:35.642
Now you progress to cleaning toilets.

1301
01:28:35.893 --> 01:28:37.561
I love you. Paul.

1302
01:28:37.895 --> 01:28:40.731
I really love you.
You're such a funny guy.

1303
01:28:41.065 --> 01:28:42.149
Hilarious.

1304
01:28:42.400 --> 01:28:45.902
Like I said. you're too much a nice guy

1305
01:28:46.279 --> 01:28:48.613
and a little bit pathetic guy.

1306
01:28:48.906 --> 01:28:50.741
It's just until she gets a new foot.

1307
01:28:50.908 --> 01:28:53.243
- When will that be?
- I don't know. The doctor said

1308
01:28:53.411 --> 01:28:54.911
a month. maybe six weeks.

1309
01:28:55.079 --> 01:28:57.080
- That's an eternity.
- I know!

1310
01:28:57.290 --> 01:28:59.041
Meantime. she's stuck with a peg leg.

1311
01:28:59.250 --> 01:29:01.168
which is almost as bad as
having nothing at all.

1312
01:29:01.252 --> 01:29:02.252
I mean. look at her!

1313
01:29:02.337 --> 01:29:04.963
She's waddling around
like a goddamn pirate.

1314
01:29:05.256 --> 01:29:06.465
(LAUGHING)

1315
01:29:06.841 --> 01:29:08.884
Paul! You no talk with Mr. Dušan.

1316
01:29:08.968 --> 01:29:10.844
You go upstair with Verónica.

1317
01:29:12.180 --> 01:29:13.722
- Paul!
- I heard you.

1318
01:29:14.182 --> 01:29:15.766
Don't worry. Paul.

1319
01:29:18.603 --> 01:29:20.437
Dušan will save you.

1320
01:29:21.105 --> 01:29:22.731
(GRUNTING)

1321
01:29:28.738 --> 01:29:30.072
(SNIFFS)

1322
01:29:32.075 --> 01:29:33.575
NGOC LAN: Wow.

1323
01:29:34.911 --> 01:29:37.079
Yeah. Miss Tran. take everything.

1324
01:29:38.998 --> 01:29:42.125
Mr. Konrad and I are
leaving day after tomorrow

1325
01:29:42.210 --> 01:29:44.044
and don't know when we'll be back.

1326
01:29:45.171 --> 01:29:46.838
Okay. good. Thank you.

1327
01:29:47.256 --> 01:29:49.174
Paul. Mr. Dušan say I take all the food.

1328
01:29:49.258 --> 01:29:50.926
You go find me big box.

1329
01:29:51.177 --> 01:29:52.177
In a minute.

1330
01:29:52.261 --> 01:29:55.138
First there's something
very important to discuss.

1331
01:29:57.225 --> 01:29:58.225
Me?

1332
01:29:58.309 --> 01:30:00.477
DUŠAN: This is the situation.

1333
01:30:00.645 --> 01:30:02.562
I don't know exactly what.

1334
01:30:02.730 --> 01:30:04.731
but something big. very big.

1335
01:30:04.816 --> 01:30:07.234
is happening
at the original small colony.

1336
01:30:07.610 --> 01:30:09.444
You know. the one in Norway.

1337
01:30:10.071 --> 01:30:13.740
They want me to go there right away
with a very important delivery.

1338
01:30:14.242 --> 01:30:15.700
It's too complicated to explain.

1339
01:30:15.785 --> 01:30:18.537
Top secret and very urgent.

1340
01:30:18.621 --> 01:30:23.500
but most important.
they are offering us very big money.

1341
01:30:24.168 --> 01:30:25.168
Very big.

1342
01:30:25.253 --> 01:30:26.753
And that means

1343
01:30:27.004 --> 01:30:31.133
we need extra help to do this quickly.
make them happy

1344
01:30:31.217 --> 01:30:33.802
and. I'm sorry to say.
we need the same excellent helper

1345
01:30:33.886 --> 01:30:35.554
who's currently helping you.

1346
01:30:35.805 --> 01:30:36.805
Him.

1347
01:30:37.140 --> 01:30:38.473
That's right. Ngoc Lan.

1348
01:30:38.558 --> 01:30:41.059
I have to go with these guys to Norway.

1349
01:30:43.688 --> 01:30:46.022
So you say

1350
01:30:46.482 --> 01:30:48.608
Paul go with you Norway?

1351
01:30:48.985 --> 01:30:50.735
That's the situation.

1352
01:30:51.237 --> 01:30:54.739
- Emergency situation!
- And deeply humanitarian.

1353
01:30:56.159 --> 01:30:57.993
PAUL: I mean. Ngoc Lan. I will

1354
01:30:58.077 --> 01:31:02.247
be able to help when I get back 100%.
and when you get the new foot. and...

1355
01:31:02.498 --> 01:31:03.999
NGOC LAN: You leave Wednesday?

1356
01:31:04.500 --> 01:31:05.500
Yes.

1357
01:31:06.794 --> 01:31:08.503
And how long you go?

1358
01:31:11.966 --> 01:31:13.967
Ten days. maybe more.

1359
01:31:19.724 --> 01:31:21.475
Okay. Yes. Norway.

1360
01:31:21.934 --> 01:31:23.685
I go Norway. too.

1361
01:31:24.103 --> 01:31:26.104
No. no. no. Not you.

1362
01:31:26.689 --> 01:31:28.023
Only Paul.

1363
01:31:28.107 --> 01:31:30.942
I go Norway. too.
Paul. you help me on the trip.

1364
01:31:32.361 --> 01:31:33.528
But you're very busy here

1365
01:31:33.613 --> 01:31:36.031
with humanitarian activities
on your own.

1366
01:31:36.532 --> 01:31:38.200
And your cleaning business!

1367
01:31:38.784 --> 01:31:41.286
Verónica and other ladies know
every place.

1368
01:31:41.370 --> 01:31:42.871
They do for me. I pay them good.

1369
01:31:42.955 --> 01:31:44.539
No problem I go.

1370
01:31:45.291 --> 01:31:47.709
Norway colony people
invite me so many time.

1371
01:31:47.793 --> 01:31:49.294
but I never go.

1372
01:31:49.378 --> 01:31:51.630
Feel so. so guilty!

1373
01:31:52.715 --> 01:31:54.466
They so nice people.

1374
01:31:55.343 --> 01:31:56.343
What?

1375
01:31:56.677 --> 01:31:58.303
Who invited you?

1376
01:31:59.805 --> 01:32:02.891
When I hospital
so long time after TV box.

1377
01:32:03.226 --> 01:32:05.310
people all over world

1378
01:32:05.478 --> 01:32:08.813
send me happy card. flower. candy.

1379
01:32:09.065 --> 01:32:10.565
Make me feel good.

1380
01:32:11.234 --> 01:32:12.651
So many letter.

1381
01:32:12.735 --> 01:32:15.237
One letter very special I never forget.

1382
01:32:15.571 --> 01:32:17.906
From Jorgen Asbjørnsen.

1383
01:32:19.575 --> 01:32:22.118
You got a letter from Jorgen Asbjørnsen?

1384
01:32:22.912 --> 01:32:24.996
Dr. Asbjørnsen write me.

1385
01:32:25.665 --> 01:32:30.168
Say he feel so. so bad
I suffer for he fault.

1386
01:32:32.004 --> 01:32:33.838
He say he painful.

1387
01:32:33.923 --> 01:32:36.675
He never think
make small so bad for people.

1388
01:32:38.511 --> 01:32:41.304
Dr. Asbjørnsen letter
make me feel so good.

1389
01:32:41.722 --> 01:32:43.223
I write letter. too.

1390
01:32:43.307 --> 01:32:46.560
Say now first time I happy be small.

1391
01:32:49.897 --> 01:32:52.899
He say me make trip go Norway any day.

1392
01:32:53.734 --> 01:32:55.652
But I too busy.

1393
01:32:55.987 --> 01:32:57.195
Always too busy.

1394
01:32:57.280 --> 01:33:00.991
Now Jesus give me special gift
go Norway.

1395
01:33:02.368 --> 01:33:03.410
(SNIFFLES)

1396
01:33:03.494 --> 01:33:06.830
Thank you. Mr. Dušan.
Thank you. Mr. Konrad.

1397
01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:11.751
Yes. I go Norway. too.

1398
01:33:11.961 --> 01:33:13.628
So happy!

1399
01:33:14.005 --> 01:33:16.172
Thank you special time.

1400
01:33:20.886 --> 01:33:22.220
(DUŠAN SNIFFLES)

1401
01:33:56.380 --> 01:33:58.534
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1402
01:34:27.203 --> 01:34:29.162
(MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

1403
01:34:58.693 --> 01:35:00.276
(THUDS ON DECK)

1404
01:35:08.703 --> 01:35:10.453
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

1405
01:35:16.877 --> 01:35:18.044
Paul. look.

1406
01:35:18.379 --> 01:35:21.381
This Jorgen Asbjørnsen and he wife.

1407
01:35:23.217 --> 01:35:26.052
Oh. my God. Jorgen Asbjørnsen?

1408
01:35:27.471 --> 01:35:28.596
Hello.

1409
01:35:28.681 --> 01:35:31.391
- It's just such an honor.
- Hello. hello.

1410
01:35:31.767 --> 01:35:32.851
NGOC LAN: See. Paul?

1411
01:35:33.519 --> 01:35:35.145
Jesus smile for me.

1412
01:35:35.229 --> 01:35:38.148
I say Paul I want visit Norway
only for meet you.

1413
01:35:38.816 --> 01:35:39.899
It's true.

1414
01:35:40.067 --> 01:35:41.776
- I'm Anne-Helene.
- Hello.

1415
01:35:42.236 --> 01:35:43.903
Please sit. Join us.

1416
01:35:44.238 --> 01:35:45.321
PAUL: Thank you.

1417
01:35:45.656 --> 01:35:47.282
We're watching the world go by.

1418
01:35:47.366 --> 01:35:48.742
PAUL: Sounds great.

1419
01:35:49.744 --> 01:35:51.911
You have no idea
how terribly grief-stricken

1420
01:35:51.996 --> 01:35:54.289
we were by Miss Tran's case.

1421
01:35:54.790 --> 01:35:58.293
Jorgen has lost so much sleep
over all the abuses.

1422
01:36:08.679 --> 01:36:10.388
JORGEN: It's humbling. huh?

1423
01:36:11.474 --> 01:36:14.559
Nature is such a patient sculptor.

1424
01:36:14.894 --> 01:36:16.728
Grinding a tiny bit

1425
01:36:16.896 --> 01:36:20.356
each day. slowly. slowly.
for thousands of years.

1426
01:36:20.441 --> 01:36:25.236
to make such a supremely
beautiful thing.

1427
01:36:27.573 --> 01:36:28.990
What a waste.

1428
01:36:31.160 --> 01:36:34.162
What a dreadful waste.

1429
01:36:44.006 --> 01:36:45.673
You'll have to excuse Jorgen.

1430
01:36:45.758 --> 01:36:49.010
These past few days
has been especially hard.

1431
01:36:49.428 --> 01:36:52.013
Such a big decision to make.
and so quickly.

1432
01:36:52.640 --> 01:36:55.433
Normally. when we visit the colony.
we like to spend

1433
01:36:55.518 --> 01:36:58.895
a few days in Henningsvær.
but then the news came.

1434
01:36:59.897 --> 01:37:00.897
And...

1435
01:37:01.065 --> 01:37:04.567
Yeah. well. here we are.
suddenly imposing on you.

1436
01:37:04.944 --> 01:37:06.945
We scarcely had the time to pack.

1437
01:37:08.072 --> 01:37:10.031
I'm sorry. wait. what news?

1438
01:37:10.699 --> 01:37:13.368
Why. the methane release in Antarctica.

1439
01:37:13.452 --> 01:37:15.411
You must know about the methane.

1440
01:37:16.455 --> 01:37:17.455
Yeah.

1441
01:37:17.790 --> 01:37:19.541
That's not new. is it? I mean...

1442
01:37:20.835 --> 01:37:22.418
New or old.

1443
01:37:23.170 --> 01:37:24.671
it's the end.

1444
01:37:25.756 --> 01:37:28.508
It's the end of everything.

1445
01:37:30.761 --> 01:37:34.722
The world has already seen
five major extinctions.

1446
01:37:35.307 --> 01:37:36.975
and now there will be another.

1447
01:37:37.434 --> 01:37:40.854
I didn't want to believe it.
none of us did.

1448
01:37:41.063 --> 01:37:45.066
but there we were in Helsinki.
big and small.

1449
01:37:45.234 --> 01:37:47.986
Climatologists. bacteriologists.

1450
01:37:48.153 --> 01:37:51.573
demographers. physicists. immunologists.

1451
01:37:51.907 --> 01:37:55.243
Twenty-six Nobel Prize winners among us.

1452
01:37:55.995 --> 01:37:58.580
We built all the models.
did all the math

1453
01:37:58.664 --> 01:38:01.583
and our conclusion was consistent.

1454
01:38:02.418 --> 01:38:05.837
Homo sapiens will soon vanish
from the Earth.

1455
01:38:06.755 --> 01:38:09.757
It is now an actuarial certainty.

1456
01:38:11.093 --> 01:38:13.428
No matter how the end will come.

1457
01:38:13.596 --> 01:38:15.805
environmental disaster.

1458
01:38:15.890 --> 01:38:20.226
pandemic disease. unbreathable air.
impotable water.

1459
01:38:20.477 --> 01:38:22.896
not enough food. nuclear winter.

1460
01:38:22.980 --> 01:38:25.815
some combination of them all.

1461
01:38:27.026 --> 01:38:32.238
relatively soon the Earth will indeed
purge itself of human life

1462
01:38:33.324 --> 01:38:36.075
and God knows how many other species.

1463
01:38:37.578 --> 01:38:38.953
Do you really mean extinction?

1464
01:38:39.038 --> 01:38:40.580
What about downsizing?

1465
01:38:40.664 --> 01:38:42.665
Yeah. yeah. too little too late.

1466
01:38:42.750 --> 01:38:45.710
Only 3% of the world has miniaturized.

1467
01:38:45.878 --> 01:38:47.837
There simply isn't enough time.

1468
01:38:50.674 --> 01:38:51.758
(CHUCKLES)

1469
01:38:51.842 --> 01:38:55.553
Not a very successful species.
these Homo sapiens.

1470
01:38:55.971 --> 01:38:58.556
even with such great intelligence.

1471
01:38:58.891 --> 01:39:01.559
Barely 200.000 years.

1472
01:39:01.894 --> 01:39:06.940
Alligator has survived 200 million years
with a brain the size of a walnut.

1473
01:39:11.654 --> 01:39:12.862
PAUL: People have been predicting

1474
01:39:12.947 --> 01:39:15.573
the end of the world
for thousands of years.

1475
01:39:16.575 --> 01:39:18.576
Now it's really happening.

1476
01:39:20.996 --> 01:39:23.414
I guess somebody
had to be right someday.

1477
01:39:24.833 --> 01:39:26.250
So sad.

1478
01:39:27.711 --> 01:39:29.045
Very sad.

1479
01:39:43.310 --> 01:39:46.562
Okay. I go sleep now. Good night. Paul.

1480
01:39:47.398 --> 01:39:49.315
Good night. Ngoc Lan.

1481
01:39:51.777 --> 01:39:53.069
(GROANS SOFTLY)

1482
01:39:53.821 --> 01:39:55.989
- You okay?
- I fine.

1483
01:39:56.407 --> 01:39:58.908
You know. maybe I should
take a look at your leg.

1484
01:39:59.076 --> 01:40:01.077
Okay. Yes. you look.

1485
01:40:05.749 --> 01:40:07.250
PAUL: Ah. yep.

1486
01:40:07.501 --> 01:40:08.668
Wow.

1487
01:40:09.336 --> 01:40:12.088
That peg is really making
the skin chafe.

1488
01:40:12.756 --> 01:40:14.132
Okay.

1489
01:40:21.765 --> 01:40:22.807
You know.

1490
01:40:23.809 --> 01:40:26.144
if somebody had told me 10 years ago

1491
01:40:26.228 --> 01:40:29.397
that one day I'd be
five inches tall and divorced

1492
01:40:29.815 --> 01:40:32.650
helping a famous Vietnamese
dissident get a new foot

1493
01:40:32.818 --> 01:40:35.278
while cruising up a fjord in Norway

1494
01:40:35.362 --> 01:40:38.072
discussing the end of the world
with Jorgen Asbjørnsen.

1495
01:40:39.408 --> 01:40:41.325
I'd have said he was crazy.

1496
01:40:43.245 --> 01:40:44.787
(NGOC LAN EXHALES)

1497
01:41:16.987 --> 01:41:18.071
I'm sorry.

1498
01:41:18.447 --> 01:41:19.864
I'm sorry. I thought...

1499
01:41:21.158 --> 01:41:22.325
Jesus. I'm such an idiot.

1500
01:41:22.868 --> 01:41:23.868
No.

1501
